        <h1>
            CSS methodology evolution
        </h1>

        <p class="intro">
            Most methodologies were honest answers to real constraints: global
            cascade, unknown specificity, slow iteration, and teams shipping in
            parallel. As the platform adds better primitives, some problems get
            cheaper—but people, ownership, and delivery risk do not disappear.
        </p>
    </section>

    <nav class="section-nav" aria-label="Article sections">
        <a href="#why-methods">Why methods existed</a>
        <a href="#what-shifted">What shifted</a>
